\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 SETUP for BACFUG jQTouch Walk Through
\b0 \
\
- You'll need ColdFusion 9 Installed\
- You'll need a web server running at localhost \
- You'll need a database running (mySQL, SQL Server, etc) or you can use Apache Derby which comes with ColdFusion\
\
1. Drag the "bacfug" folder into your localhost web root\
\
2. Create a new database schema in mySQL, MSSQL, etc (or skip this step and use Apache Derby in the ColdFusion Administrator)\
\
3. Launch the ColdFusion Administrator  usually at http://localhost/CFIDE/Administrator/\
\
4. Login and click on "Datasources"\
\
5. Add a new datasource called "jqtouch" \
\
6. Browser to http://localhost/bacfug/init.cfm\
\
7. Browse to  http://localhost/bacfug/load.cfm\
\
8. Test out your database with http://localhost/bacfug/wt09.html\
\
If you need to drop and recreate the database use this URL\
\
http://localhost/bacfug/init.cfm?refresh=true\
\
